Wireshark
Network protocol analyzer for traffic inspection

Sniffing & Spoofing
Description
Wireshark is the world's foremost network protocol analyzer. It lets you capture and interactively browse the traffic running on a computer network, showing packet details at the protocol level.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which wireshark
Install command:

sudo apt install wireshark
Basic Syntax
wireshark (GUI) or tshark (CLI)
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
wireshark

Launch GUI - Open graphical interface	Interactive analysis	
tshark -i eth0

CLI capture - Command line capture	Headless systems	
Filter: http

HTTP filter - Web traffic only	Web traffic analysis	
Filter: ip.addr == 192.168.1.1

IP filter - Specific host	Focus on one IP	
Filter: tcp.port == 443

Port filter - Specific port	Service analysis	
Filter: tcp.flags.syn == 1

SYN packets - New connections	Connection analysis	
Filter: dns

DNS traffic - Name resolution	DNS analysis	
Filter: ftp || ftp-data

FTP traffic - File transfers	FTP analysis	
Filter: http.request.method == "POST"

POST requests - Form submissions	Find login attempts	
Filter: http contains "password"

Password search - Find creds	Credential hunting	
Filter: tcp.analysis.retransmission

Retransmissions - Network issues	Network debugging	
Right-click > Follow > TCP Stream

Follow stream - Full conversation	See request/response	
