Step-by-Step Guide
1
Launch Wireshark with sudo wireshark
2
Select network interface to capture from
3
Click Start Capture (shark fin icon)
4
Generate traffic or wait for packets
5
Apply display filters to focus on interesting traffic
6
Click on packets to see details
7
Use Follow > TCP Stream to see conversations
8
Stop capture and save for later analysis
Understanding the Output
Wireshark shows three panes: packet list (summary), packet details (protocol breakdown), and packet bytes (hex dump). Colors indicate different traffic types. Red typically means issues.

Important Warnings
•
Capturing traffic on networks you don't own may be illegal
•
You may inadvertently capture sensitive data
•
Some encrypted traffic (HTTPS) can't be read directly
•
Captures can consume significant disk space
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
